# Build wiring for robotstxtr (ROBO-mzwcditw, YI3b).
#
# Compiles the package-owned translation units AND the nested vendored
# robotstxtyandex payload into a single package shared object. The vendored
# objects link in but are called by nothing yet (the public Yandex matcher
# binding is a later unit, YI4b); Yandex stays capability_unavailable.
#
# Portability / CRAN notes:
#  * OBJECTS is an explicit, enumerated list (no GNU make $(wildcard)/patsubst),
#    so no `SystemRequirements: GNU make` declaration is needed. Defining
#    OBJECTS overrides R's auto-glob of src/*, so every package-owned object
#    MUST be listed here too.
#  * The vendored objects are named at the TOP LEVEL of src/ (access_matcher.o,
#    ...) and their sources are located via VPATH below. This is deliberate:
#    `R CMD build` installs the package to render vignettes, which compiles
#    these objects, and its `cleaning src` step only removes top-level src/*.o.
#    Objects left in a nested src/ subdirectory would survive into the built
#    source tarball and trip the "checking if this is a source package" NOTE.
#    Compiling to top level keeps them under that cleanup.
#  * VPATH is a plain variable assignment (not a rule/target), so it does not
#    become make's default goal. It lets R's built-in `.cc.o` inference rule
#    find each vendored source in vendor/robotstxtyandex/src/ and compile it to
#    the matching top-level object with the standard C++17 flags — byte-for-byte
#    the same compile the implicit rule performs. No explicit recipes, no GNU
#    make features.
#  * Vendored sources reference public headers as
#    `#include "robotstxtyandex/xxx.h"`, resolved via the include path below;
#    their private sibling headers resolve same-directory (no -I needed).
#
# Keep in sync with src/Makevars.win (identical logic).

CXX_STD = CXX17

PKG_CPPFLAGS = -Ivendor/robotstxtyandex/include

VPATH = vendor/robotstxtyandex/src

OBJECTS = \
	cpp11.o \
	collector_binding.o \
	matcher_binding.o \
	reporting_robots.o \
	robots.o \
	access_matcher.o \
	crawler_selector.o \
	directive_lexer.o \
	parser_ir.o \
	physical_line_scanner.o \
	policy_engine.o \
	policy.o \
	version.o
